\begin_inset Formula $f(x,y)$
\end_inset

.
 On the other hand, vector fields 
\begin_inset Formula $x\partial_{y}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\partial_{x}$
\end_inset

 do not commute because 
\begin_inset Formula \[
x\partial_{y}\left(\partial_{x}f\right)-\partial_{x}\left(x\partial_{y}f\right)=-\partial_{y}f\neq0.\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A vector field 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{c}$
\end_inset

