\begin_layout Standard
One of the main assumptions underlying GR is that the geometry of our universe
 is curved rather than flat.
 In a curved geometry, initially parallel lines may move closer or further
 apart, and the sum of the angles of some triangles may be larger or smaller
 than 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi$
\end_inset

