 This picture leads to the general definition of an 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset


\series bold
-dimensional manifold
\series default
: a set of points 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{M}$
\end_inset

 such that each point 
\begin_inset Formula $p\in\mathcal{M}$
\end_inset

