\begin_layout Standard
Given two 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

sufficiently close
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 points 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $p'$
\end_inset

, how can we determine the tangent vector 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{v}$
\end_inset

 that represents the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

almost straight
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 line between 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $p'$
\end_inset

? We can choose some curve 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma(\tau)$
\end_inset

