A surface is embedded into a Euclidean space 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{3}$
\end_inset

.
 A short curve segment connecting two points 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{a}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{b}$
\end_inset

 is approximated by a straight line segment.
 The length of this straight line segment is computed using the Euclidean
 metric in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{3}$
\end_inset

.
