\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the index notation, the scalar product form 
\begin_inset Formula $g^{-1}$
\end_inset

 is specified by the matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $g^{\alpha\beta}$
\end_inset

, which is inverse to the matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $g_{\alpha\beta}$
\end_inset

 representing the components of the metric 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

.
\hfill

\begin_inset Formula $\blacksquare$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For a scalar function 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

, the 1-form 
\begin_inset Formula $\textrm{d}f$
\end_inset

 called the 
\series bold
gradient
\series default
 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \index{gradient}

\end_inset

of 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 acts on vectors 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{x}$
\end_inset

 as
\begin_inset Formula \[
\left(\textrm{d}f\right)\circ\mathbf{x}\equiv\mathbf{x}\circ f,\]

\end_inset

and the corresponding vector field 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{g}^{-1}(\textrm{d}f)$
\end_inset

 may be called the 
\series bold
contravariant gradient
\series default
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

.
\begin_inset LatexCommand \index{contravariant gradient}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Example: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For a vector field 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{x}$
\end_inset

 and a scalar function 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

, we have
\begin_inset Formula \[
\mathbf{x}\circ f=g(\mathbf{x},\hat{g}^{-1}\textrm{d}f)=g^{-1}(\hat{g}\mathbf{x},\textrm{d}f).\]

\end_inset

 The derivative of a scalar function 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 in the direction of the vector 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{g}^{-1}\textrm{d}f$
\end_inset

, i.e.\InsetSpace ~
the scalar quantity 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\hat{g}^{-1}\textrm{d}f\right)\circ\phi$
\end_inset

, can be also expressed as
\begin_inset Formula \[
\left(\hat{g}^{-1}\textrm{d}f\right)\circ\phi=g^{-1}(\textrm{d}f,\textrm{d}\phi)=\left(\hat{g}^{-1}\textrm{d}\phi\right)\circ f.\]

\end_inset


\hfill

\begin_inset Formula $\blacksquare$
