\begin_layout Standard
A null geodesic 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma(\tau)$
\end_inset

 remains a geodesic when the metric is rescaled by a conformal transformation,
 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{g}=e^{2\lambda}g$
\end_inset

, under a suitable change of the affine parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $\tau\rightarrow f(\tau)$
\end_inset

, such that the new affine tangent vector is 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{-2\lambda}\dot{\boldsymbol{\gamma}}$
\end_inset

.
 In other words, the shape of a null geodesic is
\series bold
 conformally invariant
\series default
.
 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \index{conformal invariance!of null geodesics}

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

