\begin_layout Subsection
Geodesics extremize proper length
\begin_inset LatexCommand \label{sub:Derivation of geodesic equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In Riemannian geometry, when the metric is positive-definite, sufficiently
 short geodesic curves have an important property: they are curves of shortest
 length among all curves connecting two given points.
 In GR, the metric is not positive-definite, so geodesic curves extremize
 the 
\emph on
proper length
\emph default
.
 In this section we derive the geodesic equation from the corresponding
 variational principle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
