\begin_layout Standard
A conformal diagram provides a visualization of the causal structure of
 a spacetime because the null geodesics remain straight lines after the
 conformal transformation, and because the entire spacetime is drawn as
 a finite figure in a plane.
 For instance, it is easy to see the entire domain that can receive signals
 from a given spacetime point.
\end_layout

