a(t,x_{1},x_{2},x_{3})=\frac{1}{\eta(t)+\xi(t)\sum_{i=1}^{3}\left(x_{i}-\beta_{i}(t)\right)^{2}},\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{i},\eta,\xi$
\end_inset

 are arbitrary functions of time.
 Nevertheless, in many cases a 3+1-dimensional spacetime can be adequately
 represented by a suitable 1+1-dimensional slice, at least for the purpose
