 For instance, a spherically symmetric spacetime is visualized using the
 time-radial half-plane 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ t,r\right\} $
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $r\geq0$
\end_inset

, where each point stands for a 2-sphere of radius 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

.
 A conformal diagram is then drawn for the reduced 1+1-dimensional spacetime.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The reduced conformal diagram is meaningful only if the null geodesics in
