\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{B}$
\end_inset

 must be on the future side from 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{H}$
\end_inset

.
 We also know that null surface is generated by null geodesics (see Sec.\InsetSpace ~

\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{sub:Null-functions-generate}

\end_inset

).
 Suppose that a null generator 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

