\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

 is symmetric and transverse to 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{n}$
\end_inset

, we find
\begin_inset Formula \begin{align*}
\Gamma(\mathbf{x})\Gamma(\mathbf{y})\mathbf{z} & =\mathbf{n}K(\Gamma(\mathbf{y})\mathbf{z},\mathbf{x})=\mathbf{n}K(\mathbf{n}(...),...)=0,\\
