\series default
 
\begin_inset LatexCommand \index{Hamiltonian constraint}

\end_inset

or the 
\series bold
energy constraint
\series default
, while 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta\mathcal{H}/\delta s_{a}=0$
\end_inset

 is called the 
\series bold
momentum constraint
\series default
.
 We find (perhaps with surprise) that the constraints make the Hamiltonian
 itself vanish, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{H}=0$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

