If 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega$
\end_inset

 is a 2-form and 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega$
\end_inset

 is the 1-form corresponding to the vector 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{v}=\hat{g}^{-1}\omega$
\end_inset

, then
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
\omega\wedge*\Omega=-*(\iota_{\mathbf{v}}\Omega),\label{eq:omega wedge star Omega rel}\end{equation}

\end_inset

where both sides are 3-forms.
\end_layout

