\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{v}=\mathbf{u}$
\end_inset

 then 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{L}$
\end_inset

 is itself a proper rotation, so we can still say that 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{L}$
\end_inset

 is a product of a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

trivial
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 boost and a rotation.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{v}\neq\mathbf{u}$
\end_inset

, we can find a boost 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{L}_{1}$
\end_inset

 that brings 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{u}$
\end_inset

 into 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{v}$
\end_inset

.
