\end_inset

 and also into 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{T}\mathbf{u}_{1}\wedge...\wedge\hat{T}\mathbf{u}_{n}$
\end_inset

.
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{T}$
\end_inset

 is a linear map, 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\hat{T}\mathbf{u}_{j}=\sum_{k}U_{jk}\hat{T}\mathbf{v}_{k},\]

\end_inset

so the substitution of 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{T}\mathbf{u}_{j}=\sum_{k}U_{jk}\hat{T}\mathbf{v}_{k}$
\end_inset

 into 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{T}\mathbf{u}_{1}\wedge...\wedge\hat{T}\mathbf{u}_{n}$
\end_inset

 yields terms 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\hat{T}\mathbf{v}_{1}\wedge...\hat{T}\mathbf{v}_{n}\]

\end_inset

with the same coefficients as the substitution of 
