 It follows that a nonzero contribution is possible only if the set 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ k_{1},...,k_{n}\right\} $
\end_inset

 is a permutation of the set 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \sigma(1),...,\sigma(n)\right\} $
\end_inset

